text: The canton of Serris is an administrative division of the Seine-et-Marne department, in northern France. It was created at the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015. Its seat is in Serris.Décret n° 2014-186 du 18 février 2014 portant délimitation des cantons dans le département de Seine-et-Marne It consists of the following communes: #Bailly-Romainvilliers #Bouleurs #Boutigny #Chessy #Condé-Sainte-Libiaire #Couilly-Pont-aux-Dames #Coulommes #Coupvray #Coutevroult #Crécy-la-Chapelle #Esbly #La Haute-Maison #Magny-le-Hongre #Montry #Quincy-Voisins #Saint-Fiacre #Saint-Germain-sur-Morin #Sancy #Serris #Tigeaux #Vaucourtois #Villemareuil #Villiers-sur-Morin #Voulangis ==References== Category:Cantons of Seine-et- Marne
title: Canton of Serris
